{"id":38099,"title":"Extraction of high molecular weight DNA from aphids and other sap-feeding insects for long-read sequencing.","title_html":"<p>Extraction of high molecular weight DNA from aphids and other sap-feeding insects for long-read sequencing.<\/p>","image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/c6bc6ee3da0d15d9afae196ce3c907a4158cf881919d7aec1f83e2307336805e\/cbtm2ky6.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/c6bc6ee3da0d15d9afae196ce3c907a4158cf881919d7aec1f83e2307336805e\/cbtm2ky6.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.bhftj3nn","doi_status":2,"uri":"extraction-of-high-molecular-weight-dna-from-aphid-bhftj3nn","type_id":1,"template_id":4,"published_on":1591971619,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"cited_protocols":[],"version_id":0,"created_on":1591970611,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Sam Mugford","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[{"affiliation":null,"url":null,"is_default":1}],"username":"sam-mugford","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png"},"badges":[{"id":3,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg"},"name":"Power author!"},{"id":6,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/accelerator.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/accelerator.svg"},"name":"Science accelerator"}],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":17,"authors":[{"name":"Roland Wouters","affiliation":"John Innes Centre, Norwich, UK","affiliations":[],"username":"m4tle112y1y4qle1","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Sam Mugford","affiliation":"John Innes Centre, Norwich, UK","affiliations":[],"username":"sam-mugford","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Roberto Biello","affiliation":"John Innes Centre, Norwich, UK","affiliations":[],"username":"m4tle122r1x4sle1","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/006.png"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Darren Heavens","affiliation":"Earlham Institute (EI), Norwich, UK","affiliations":[],"username":"darren-heavens","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/003.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/003.png"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Saskia Hogenhout","affiliation":"John Innes Centre, Norwich, UK","affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"is_owner":1,"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_claim_authorship":0,"can_accept_authorship":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"fork_id":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/view\/extraction-of-high-molecular-weight-dna-from-aphid-bhftj3nn","forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"753CAC30ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","state_version_id":74,"steps":[{"id":960099,"guid":"7F07D820ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8ECB79BC24454337ACD670CDE64739C7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2DC1ACA32B9B4A9CA48DB5A99050A076","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Grind approx. 10mg (20 frozen aphids; originated from a single female, one froghopper) in a 1.5ml Eppendorf tube, with a plastic pestle, pre-cooled in liquid nitrogen. Ensure that tissue remains frozen throughout. When grinding the samples do not turn the pestle, but crush the aphids via an up-down movement.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960100,"guid":"9338E960ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960099,"previous_guid":"7F07D820ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E183CA45FED34FFCA7D0A4A8BE2747DE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BA37A3DBCE1445F3825F3EE638B5D921","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 600 \u00b5l of reagent 1, with RNAse added. Leave the plastic pestle in the tube during the addition of buffer to ensure tissue stuck to the pestle is not lost, mix thoroughly by agitating the pestle. Remove the pestle, taking care to leave as much material inside the tube as possible. Incubate at 37\u00b0 C for 30 minutes, with occasional mixing by inversion.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960101,"guid":"9AFC5E70ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960100,"previous_guid":"9338E960ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"63610118BF6F4D1D8801D19E188B9E6C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EC1163D4F45F4C9291CBC8987071AC0C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 200 \u00b5l of reagent 2 and mix by inversion until a consistent solution in acquired. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960102,"guid":"A34222E0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960101,"previous_guid":"9AFC5E70ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"42576E2CC37B42F2849DF1A3BFEA3BA5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"313050A0E64948F2979FFB0B36D96A5E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">(Optional) Add 10 \u00b5l proteinase K (600U\/ml), incubate at 55\u00b0 C for 2 hours with occasional mixing by inversion.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960103,"guid":"AE32E310ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960102,"previous_guid":"A34222E0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"93301779047840EAB6893DB4341875FD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"11D204FC57D74786A86ADC47ECA8A1D2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Alternatively, if not using proteinase K, incubate at 65\u00b0 C for 10 minutes with regular mixing by inversion.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960104,"guid":"BDB9A620ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960103,"previous_guid":"AE32E310ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"32E945D9E64E4DCBBA3D7A09C23B01F3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"93FF616D35AD400EBA996BEE7B3CF954","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Place samples on ice for 20 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960105,"guid":"C6675420ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960104,"previous_guid":"BDB9A620ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"33062F8AA29748D8BA0B4B155E287492","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C2D4D4D0CAEA49029BD6729349DBD79E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 500 \u00b5l of pre-cooled chloroform at -20\u00b0 C, and 100 \u00b5l of Nucleon PhytoPure DNA extraction resin suspension, mix by gentle shaking and inversion and mix the sample on a rotator disk for 10 minutes on room temperature. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960106,"guid":"C88C2FF0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960105,"previous_guid":"C6675420ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C047B1B5ADB6419DA3B951C09B3CF7A5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4CB77992EB6B4CB286D238F30805D4A4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge in a bench-top microfuge (1,300 G) for 10 minutes. Transfer the upper aqueous phase to a new tube. Take care not to disturb the interface. Be conservative, and leave some of the upper phases behind rather than carrying over chloroform or resin contamination.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960107,"guid":"D21C75C0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960106,"previous_guid":"C88C2FF0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"69F1D49C27B24CB1BEA3D3F65619E613","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0474FD419B224F6EBBFAAAA170A74CD2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">(Optional) Add the upper phase to 0.05 X volumes of 3M Na OAc (pH 5.2)<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960108,"guid":"D4419FB0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960107,"previous_guid":"D21C75C0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5DC3F08288894E39846D1661ACEA3CFB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5B030097DB754CD18978B58A52F7017B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1 volume of pre-cooled isopropanol at -20\u00b0 C. Add one drop at a time. Mix the tube by inversion. Mix by inversion and incubate at -20\u00b0 C for 15 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960109,"guid":"DB833A90ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960108,"previous_guid":"D4419FB0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"17B7DD33AD684D62852391F592141E65","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"86190472060C4155852D15B6D95788B1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge in a bench-top microfuge (4,000 G) for 10 minutes. Discard the supernatant without disturbing the pellet. Put the Eppendorf top-down on a paper roll to dry the sample further.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960110,"guid":"E09C0200ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960109,"previous_guid":"DB833A90ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7FF5C3FB4F3B412E984961D87578930A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9EA3A670E4894E19A5BC2802C521D961","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash the pellet in 1ml of freshly made 70% ethanol. Inverse the tube five times and centrifuge in a bench-top microfuge (4,000 G) for 20 minutes to collect the pellet. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960111,"guid":"E60C5F50ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960110,"previous_guid":"E09C0200ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A7DD14E368104A7CB78330A78378A924","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5CBB8B79B00C4D17B64507179307EA6D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">(Optional) repeat the wash step 2 more times.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960112,"guid":"EA8F2850ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960111,"previous_guid":"E60C5F50ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"ED5681A3F8CD44B5B4107F059897042B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"73027F3F94FF432AA7684603DD7BD496","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pour off the ethanol without disturbing the pellet and dry the sample by putting the Eppendorf top-down on a paper roll. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960113,"guid":"EE8BD160ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960112,"previous_guid":"EA8F2850ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8EDFA30F72E645BF9451405AFE81334C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"00C82F7BB7FE495AB068E2A7E11E6373","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend the pellet in 100 \u03bcl water, or TE.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960114,"guid":"F0C08BB0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960113,"previous_guid":"EE8BD160ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2EB826F9D1F74E18AEB48119500C09DC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6DE33A076603403E8F63566FAE6534E9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Assess the quality of DNA by electrophoresis and spectrophotometry. A single, high-molecular-weight band should be visible, a smear at lower molecular weight indicates fragmentation and\/or RNA contamination. Absorbance ratio of 260:280 and 260:230 should both be 1.8 or greater. If you suspended the pellet in TE, ensure than you blank the spectrophotometer with TE. Determine the concentration of the DNA using a fluorescent dye-binding based method such as the Qubit (Invitrogen).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":960115,"guid":"F597DD50ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","previous_id":960114,"previous_guid":"F0C08BB0ACB511EA9F2D957E09CEA266","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C9CDA0EFF25A42A4BB38F3BD66CCC3BB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"40AD7F98F3584C82BABDA3FD1024C5C8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Asses the molecular weight of the DNA sample by checking the DNA fragment sizes on the Agilent FEMTO-pulse Fragment Analyzer, or by PFGE.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Chromosome-scale genome assembly usually requires the use of long-read sequencing technologies such as PacBio or ONT MinION. However, the development of suitable DNA extraction methods that can yield high molecular weight DNA suitable these platforms can be problematic and time-consuming. We found that some traditional DNA extraction methods that are suitable for short-read sequencing platforms did not produce satisfactory results using long-read sequencing technologies with aphids or other sap-feeding hemipteran insects. We hypothesised that plant-derived components of the aphid\u2019s diet might inhibit the sequencing chemistry. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Here we present a method suitable for extraction of high-molecular DNA for long-read sequencing of aphids and other sap-feeding insects. We employed the Illustra Nucleon Phytopure DNA extraction kit designed to remove plant-specific contaminants. We were able to consistently recover very high molecular weight DNA that was compatible with library preparation and sequencing by PacBio or ONT MinION. The protocol presented here describes the use of this plant-DNA extraction kit optimised to obtain high molecular weight DNA from insect samples.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>We have used this method across a range of aphid species, leafhoppers and froghoppers (spittlebugs). It has enabled sequencing and - in most cases -chromosome-level assembly of genomes from the green peach aphid <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Myzus persicae <\/span><span>(1), the pea aphid <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Acyrthosiphon pisum<\/span><span> (1), the woolly apple aphid, <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Eriosoma lanigerum <\/span><span>(2), and the common meadow spittlebug <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Philaenus spumarius<\/span><span> (3). <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1. Chromosome-scale genome assemblies of aphids reveal extensively rearranged autosomes and long-term conservation of the X chromosome<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Thomas C.Mathers, Roland H. M.Wouters, Sam T.Mugford, DavidSwarbreck, CockVan Oosterhout, Saskia A.Hogenhout<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">bioRxiv 2020.03.24.006411; doi: https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1101\/2020.03.24.006411 <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>2. A chromosome-level genome assembly of the woolly apple aphid, <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Eriosoma lanigerum<\/span><span> (Hausmann) (Hemiptera: Aphididae)<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">RobertoBiello, ArchanaSingh, Cindayniah J.Godfrey, FelicidadFern\u00e1ndez Fern\u00e1ndez, Sam T.Mugford, GlenPowell, Saskia A.Hogenhout, Thomas C.Mathers<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">bioRxiv 2020.05.29.121947; doi: https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1101\/2020.05.29.121947 <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. Draft genome assembly version 1 of the meadow spittlebug Philaenus spumarius (Linnaeus, 1758) (Hemiptera, Aphrophoridae) (Version 1) [Data set]. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Roberto Biello, Thomas C. Mathers, Sam T. Mugford, Qun Liu, Ana S. B. Rodrigues, Ana Carina Neto, Maria Teresa Rebelo; Oct\u00e1vio S. Paulo; Sofia G. Seabra; Saskia A. Hogenhout. (2020). Zenodo. http:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.3368385<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1591971619}